HEADWORD: osteocolla
<hw>os`te*o*col"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Osteo-</ets> + Gr. <?/ glue.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of glue obtained from bones.</def>
<rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A cellular calc tufa, which in some places forms
incrustations on the stems of plants, -- formerly supposed to have the
quality of uniting fractured bones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Osteocomma</ent>⟦br⟧
